1.title: First Comes Marriage, Then Comes Love Pt. 1
1.plot: The experts have chosen four couples to marry as complete strangers. Not only will they have to deal with the anxiety of planning a wedding and marrying someone they've never met before, but some face devastating disapproval from their families.

2.title: First Comes Marriage, Then Comes Love Pt. 2
2.plot: Married at First Sight returns for a brand-new season in Philadelphia and kicks off with an in-depth exploration of the matchmaking process. When the experts meet to select each couple to marry each other as strangers, tensions flare and a final decision seems impossible.

3.title: Married at Second Sight
3.plot: Two more couples put their faith in the hands of the experts and get married at first sight; one couple has a shocking revelation; all four couples celebrate their new marriages with the help of family and friends at their wedding receptions.

4.title: Strangers in Paradise
4.plot: The four married couples are whisked away to Costa Rica for their honeymoons; while enjoying grand adventures in paradise, they discover that their new spouses might not be as perfect as they initially thought.

5.title: 'Til Mud Do Us Part
5.plot: The four couples enjoy their final few days on their honeymoons; as some grow closer, others hit major bumps in the road with their stranger spouses.

6.title: Honey, I'm Home?
6.plot: Returning from their honeymoons, the four couples face huge challenges as they move in with their new spouses.

1.title: Matchmaking
1.plot: A team of relationship experts aim to match three couples to get married at first sight. Once the matches are made, the couples have less than one week to prepare for their weddings without knowing anything about their future spouse.

2.title: The Weddings
2.plot: A team of relationship experts have matched six singles who have failed to find love and have agreed to marry a total stranger. The first time the couples meet is at their wedding ceremony. Will they all have the courage to say "I do"?

3.title: The Honeymoons
3.plot: The newlyweds met for the first time at their wedding and now, within 24 hours of saying "I do", head off on their honeymoons. Will the time alone bring these couples, still strangers, closer together or tear them apart?

4.title: Moving In
4.plot: The newlyweds have known each other for less than a week but now decide where to live and move in together.

5.title: Everyday Life
5.plot: Having just moved in together, the three couples are now facing the challenges of living with their new spouse who they barely know. When their busy schedules start to cause conflict, who will make time for their new marriages and who won't?

6.title: Intimacy
6.plot: The couples deal with issues involving intimacy, trust and emotional connection.

7.title: Social Life
7.plot: Our three couples take the next step and attempt to merge their new marriages with their old social lives. Some friends and families are more accepting than others. Dr. Pepper Schwartz visits all three couples to see who is really making the effort to integrate their worlds versus who is still keeping their distance. Monet wants Vaughn to hang out with her girlfriends. Doug invites his parents over for dinner so his mother, who is skeptical of Jamie, can start to get to know her better. 8.title: Conflict & Resolution
8.plot: Cortney confronts Jason about why he's not introducing her to his ailing mother. Jason continues to keep up his guard, and Cortney is starting to worry if she can ever break down his walls. Monet has surgery and Vaughn's mother pays them a visit. Just as Jamie was letting Doug in, she catches him in a trust-shattering lie. Are their marriages strong enough to withstand these tests? All couples go to see Dr. Joseph Cilona to work through these hard issues and see if they can save their marriages.

9.title: Last Chance at Romance
9.plot: One month into marriage, the three couples are only days away from the end of the experiment. Spiritual advisor Greg Epstein advises the newlyweds to use their remaining days to do something romantic for one another to help them decide whether to stay married or get divorced. After Vaughn and Monet make a breakthrough in communication, they enjoy a "first date" and focus on reconnecting. Jason and Cortney have dinner on a boat and exchange thoughtful gifts, but only one of them is convinced they're a perfect match. Jamie recreates her wedding photos with Doug, and ...

10.title: The Big Decision
10.plot: The five weeks are over and time draws near for the couples to decide whether or not they want to stay married or get a divorce. In these last moments of the experiment, Monet gives it her all for love by finally cooking a homemade dinner for Vaughn. Is it too little too late or will it be enough to bring them together after all they've been through? Even though Cortney seems to be dedicated to her marriage, she prepares herself for heartbreak as Jason continues to keep his guard up. 11.title: Casting Special
11.plot: This hour long special takes an in-depth look at the casting process for a groundbreaking social experiment, where a team of relationship experts set out to arrange three marriages. If the experts are successful, the couples will not meet until their wedding ceremony. Once married, the couples will live together for five weeks before deciding if they want to stay married or get a divorce.

12.title: Lost Footage Special
12.plot: See the three married couples in a way you haven't seen them before. New unseen moments from the weddings to the honeymoons, as well as bonus footage of all three couples.

13.title: Reunion Special
13.plot: Six months have passed since this social experiment started, and the three couples met at the altar. Anything could have happened. Host Kevin Frasier and the four Married At First Sight experts get the chance to catch up with the couples and ask them the questions America wants answered. Which couples are still together? Have Doug and Jamie had sex yet? Have Jason and Cortney met each other's families? Have Vaughn and Monet talked since the last day of the experiment? 1.title: Matchmaking Special
1.plot: In this radical social experiment, over 7,000 singles applied to be matched by a team of experts to be married at first sight. This special is an in-depth exploration of the matchmaking process and introduces the experiment, the experts and the candidates brave enough to marry a stranger. If the experts succeed, three couples will not meet until they say "I do" at their wedding ceremony.

2.title: Wedding Preparations
2.plot: A team of experts combine their research with the hopes of matching three couples to get married at first sight.

3.title: The Weddings
3.plot: Six singles who have tried everything to find love but have not succeeded, have agreed to put their fate in the hands of four experts and will take the most extreme step yet: marry a total stranger.

4.title: The Wedding Night and Morning After
4.plot: Three couples longing for love and commitment just said "I do" to a complete stranger. The wedding celebration ends and the couples head to their bridal suite to spend their very first night alone together as married strangers. Will intimacy grow between the couples on their wedding night or will they feel even more like strangers? And less than 24 hours after they meet, they head off to their honeymoon destinations.

5.title: Honeymoons
5.plot: The newlyweds met and married as strangers. They have known each other for just a few days yet are already on their honeymoons. In this extreme social experiment, viewers will see if romance develops...or not.

6.title: The Holidays
6.plot: The three couples who married as strangers return from their honeymoons to face the festive holiday period together as husband and wife. The newlyweds have known each other for less than a week yet must combine their holiday traditions. Tensions run high over the holiday season and this could make or break their marriages.

7.title: Moving In
7.plot: The dust has settled from the holidays and now it's time for the three couples who married as strangers to decide where to live. Location of their new home becomes a stressful situation for all three couples. Tensions rise as viewers see who is and who is not prepared to make sacrifices and ultimately to make a life-changing move.

8.title: Happy New Year
8.plot: In just two weeks of knowing each other, three couples met and married at the altar, honeymooned, celebrated the holidays and moved in together. Now, they prepare to bring in the New Year for the first time as husband and wife.

9.title: Adjusting to Married Life
9.plot: Three newlywed couples who met and married as strangers just three weeks ago have honeymooned, dealt with the holidays, set up a new home and celebrated the New Year together. With the honeymoon period well over, they face the challenges of everyday life as a married couple. Will this time alone feel like a breath of fresh air or a black cloud hovering over their heads?

10.title: Conflict
10.plot: Three newlywed couples that married at first sight must learn to cope with the conflicts arising in their relationships. Psychologist, Dr. Joseph Cilona, spends time with the couples helping them come to terms with their new lives and helping them to work through issues threatening to destroy their marriages.

11.title: Intimacy
11.plot: Three couples who married as strangers open up to sexologist Dr. Logan Levkoff, talking about sex and intimacy, both key components of a happy marriage. Some couples are struggling more than others in this area. Can Dr. Levkoff help guide the couples toward a healthy intimate relationship?

12.title: Lifestyle
12.plot: The three couples who married at first sight four weeks ago have gone on a honeymoon, spent the holidays together.

13.title: Last Chance for Romance
13.plot: Five weeks into married life and the three couples are a week away from deciding if they want to stay married or get a divorce. Spiritual advisor, Greg Epstein, encourages the couples to work hard on their relationship, and with the experiment drawing close to an end, this could be just the beginning of their marriages.

14.title: The Big Decision
14.plot: The six weeks have come to an end and the three couples must now decide whether or not they want to stay married or get a divorce. Brought together by the experts, the couples are now in control of their fate. Will any of the couples choose to stay married? Has the experiment been a success? The couples reveal their decisions to the experts.

15.title: 6 Months Later, Part 1
15.plot: Six months have passed since three couples met and married as strangers. Host, Kevin Frazier catches up with the couples and experts who matched them to ask the questions America can't wait to find out.

16.title: 6 Months Later, Part 2
16.plot: Six months have passed since three couples met and married as strangers. Host, Kevin Frazier catches up with the couples and experts who matched them to ask the questions America can't wait to find out.

0.title: Matchmaking Special
0.plot: Married at First, the extreme social experiment returns. Over 20,000 candidates have applied to be matched by a team of relationship experts. This in-depth exploration of the matchmaking process, introduces the experts, experiment and the candidates brave enough to marry a stranger. 1.title: Wedding Preparation
1.plot: Married at First Sight returns for season three. In this daring social experiment, six singles will marry a complete stranger. The experts combine their research and decide which three couples to match.

2.title: The Weddings
2.plot: Six courageous singles that have been unlucky in love have entrusted four relationship experts with the biggest decision of their lives; today they will meet their match at their wedding as they vow to legally marry as strangers. Will it be love at first sight or a wedding fright? Tres has a surprise for Vanessa at the alter; Samantha experiences wedding jitters and wonders if she will be able to walk down the aisle; and David is instantly attracted to his beautiful match, but will his bride share his feelings?

3.title: Wedding Night
3.plot: The newlyweds have just married as strangers. They are alone for the very first time on their wedding night before heading off on their honeymoons. Will their time alone in the sun spark intimacy or will it leave them feeling cold to each other? Vanessa questions Tres' commitment to marriage; Neil is faced with Samantha's brutal honesty; David and Ashley are optimistic about their future together.

4.title: Honeymoons
4.plot: Three couples married as strangers are getting to know each other on their honeymoons. Will the couples experience blissful harmony or will sparks fly in the sun? David tries to encourage Ashley to open up; Vanessa must overcome her fears in order for her and Tres to move forward; Samantha and Neil struggle with communication.

5.title: Moving In
5.plot: The couples move into their new homes.

6.title: Meet the In-Laws
6.plot: In just one week three couples have married as strangers, honeymooned and moved in together. It's Father's Day weekend, so it's the perfect time for the couple's to spend time with their in-laws. Sociologist, Dr. Pepper Schwartz, visits each couple and helps them adjust to married life. Intimacy develops between Tres and Vanessa; Neil bonds with Samantha's dad. Ashley supports David as Father's Day brings back memories of losing his dad.

7.title: Intimacy Part 1
7.plot: Just two weeks ago the couples were strangers, but not they are married and have set up a home together. Sexologist, Dr. Logan Levkoff, pays each couple a visit to help them tackle issues surrounding emotional and physical intimacy. Tres and Vanessa decide to share a bathroom together; David plucks up the courage to make a move on Ashley; Samantha and Neil question their living situation.

8.title: Breaking Down Barriers
8.plot: The three married couples first met at their wedding three weeks ago. Psychologist, Dr. Joseph Cilona, spends time with the couples helping them to communicate effectively together, open up with each other and constructively resolve their conflicts. Neil struggles with the adjustment of living with Samantha and her roommate; Vanessa struggles with fears of abandonment and Tres learns more about Vanessa from her mom; Ashley finally reveals her true feelings to David.

9.title: Making Memories
9.plot: Three couples married as strangers less than four weeks ago and have already created memories that will last a lifetime. Spiritual advisor, Greg Epstein, counsels them to help deepen bonds, increase joy in their relationships and create more happy memories. Samantha and Neil work on their communication; David tries to come to terms with the revelation that Ashley is not physically attracted to him; Tres and Vanessa discuss their thoughts on having children.

10.title: Celebrations
10.plot: Three couples married as strangers four weeks ago. It's Fourth of July and the celebrations go off with a bang. Vanessa feels threatened by Tres' friendship with another woman; Samantha starts to understand Neil better after spending time with his friends; Ashley confronts David after she discovers he texted another woman.

11.title: Intimacy Part 2
11.plot: After meeting at their wedding, the three couples have been married for five weeks. After discovering David texted another woman, Ashley needs time alone. David travels to Buffalo to seek support from his brother and visit his father's grave. Tres and Vanessa make an effort to be romantic together; Neil and Samantha move into a new home together.

12.title: Last Chance for Romance
12.plot: The experiment is almost over for the couples who married as strangers. Tres and Vanessa's romantic trip away takes an unexpected turn and is cut short. Time apart makes Samantha realize how much she misses Neil. David works hard to regain Ashley's trust and save his marriage after she discovered he texted another woman.

13.title: Final Decision Part 1
13.plot: Six weeks ago three couples married as perfect strangers. After, marrying, honeymooning, moving in together and sharing their lives the social experiment comes to an end. Experts matched the couples but now the brides and grooms must decide for themselves if they want to stay married or get a divorce?

14.title: Final Decision Part 2
14.plot: Six weeks ago three couples married as perfect strangers. After, marrying, honeymooning, moving in together and sharing their lives the social experiment comes to an end. Experts matched the couples but now the brides and grooms must decide for themselves if they want to stay married or get a divorce? Part 2 of 2.

15.title: 6 Months Later
15.plot: Six months have passed since three couples met and married as strangers. In this one-hour special, the Season 3 couples meet with Dr. Pepper Schwartz in Atlanta to discuss their experiences and reveal what has happened since viewers last saw them.

14.title: Till Death Do Us Part

15.title: After the Decision
